reviews.text: One of the many magnificent cathedrals that we visited. All are a bit similar to each other. Always feel guilty about spending so little time appreciating the design and workmanship.  Hard to miss if walking around, it is near the main square. Good to sit for a while and admire the surroundings.

This place was nice as all I'd ever seen. The architecture was great and almost larger than life, but it was not overdone, as some cathedrals are.  The inside was nothing short of heavenly. The effigies and ornamentation was beautiful, while not being too grandscale that the point of worship was offset by the magnificence of the decor.
Magnificent building , well spent time , plenty of rich history, highly advised to pay a visit👍
An interesting place with many famous painter and artist paints and arts.
Beautiful from the inside and out.  This masterpiece was often the view my family enjoyed daily. Very fond memories.  God bless.

Nice community
Just heard about it..
Best Commerzbank ATMs in town
Unglaublich aber Wahr Aus Politischen Gründen können wir ihnen kein Girokonto eröffnen dann will man auch den genauen Grund hören und wieder Aus Politischen Gründen

Als es um Kontoeröffnung ging war ich freudig überrascht. Kompetenz freundlich zuvorkommend. Ich habe mich getäuscht.
Niemand zu erreichen.. Ingelheim setzt dem ganzen die Krone auf. Ständig sind die Geld und Konto Automaten kaputt. Auch die Dame in der Filiale bringt unübersehbar Desinteresse den Kunden gegenüber.
Wäre  angebracht, einem vertrauensvollen erfahrenen Bankkaufmann - Mann - diese Filiale zu lenken und zu leiten.
Dass diese Automaten  Störungen endlich ein Ende haben

Ich würde gerne Minus-Sterne vergeben, dies ist leider ja nicht möglich. Ich bin seit 11 Jahren bei der Commerzbank Kundin und hatte in dieser Zeit, nie irgendwelche Probleme, weder was Kundenfreundlichkeit, noch Erreichbarkeit der Hotline oder der Mitarbeiter angeht. Dies hat sich in der letzten Zeit drastisch verändert. Von Kundenfreundlichkeit und - service nichts zu spüren. Ich versuche seit einem Monat mein Sparkonto aufzulösen und das Geld auf mein Girokonto (ebenfalls bei der Commerzbank) zu überweisen. Eine normale Überweisung dauert in der Regel 1 Tag, nicht so bei der Commerzbank, da warte ich seit 3 Wochen und noch immer ist kein Ende in Sicht. Nachdem ich täglich mehrfach nachtelefoniert und immer wieder mehr als 45 Minuten in der Warteschleife der Zentrale hing, um dann so qualifizierte Aussagen zu bekommen wie:"da können wir Ihnen leider nicht helfen, da müssen Sie sich an Ihre Filiale wenden." Ja ach, die erreicht man mindestens genauso gut, entweder geht niemand ans Telefon oder man bekommt gesagt es wird sich gekümmert und trotzdem passiert nichts. Und seit dieser Woche, kommt die Ansage, wenn ich die Idsteiner Filiale bzw direkt die Beraterin anrufe, dass die Nummer nicht vergeben sei...erstaunlich da hab ich die letzten Wochen mehrmals täglich drauf angerufen...absolute Frechheit und Servicewüste, mir wird mein Geld vorenthalten, so etwas habe ich noch nie erlebt. Allein die Tatsache, dass die Commerzbank bald 1 Monat brauch um eine Überweisung innerhalb ihrer eigenen Bank zu machen, ist DAS Armutszeugnis schlechthin. Da ich es leid bin, permanent in die Filiale zu gehen um mir dann pampige unfreundliche Aussagen anzuhören (junge Dame in der Mainzer Filiale, die offensichtlich ihren Job nicht mag) oder unqualifizierte Antworten über die Hotline oder gar keine bei der Idsteiner Filiale, werde ich jetzt meinen Anwalt zu Rate ziehen, damit sich dann hoffentlich langsam was bewegt. Ich bin längste Zeit Kundin gewesen, werde sobald das durch ist, mein Konto leer machen und zu einer Bank wechseln für die Service kein Fremdwort ist!

Beautiful castle
Awesome.  They hold regular carnival committee meetings here during the carnival season starting on 11 November at 11.11am.
Cool location

Excellent museum at the birthplace of Johannes Gutenberg, the inventor of efficient movable type. Most description is in German but there is an impressive English audio guide you can hire. 

One less star due to not accepting card payments.
Very nice museum. Nicely done exhibits, and there are even educational videod and a demo! You will need a few hours if you want to see the whole thing carefully, and it is worth seeing.
Interesting place to learn about print history. Amazing antique books including the first bibles

Really good museum and not expensive at all. It is really well located and also easy to spot on. But apart from the audio guide most of the informations are available only in German which contribute negatively to the experience. The Gothenburg Bible's are located on the 2 floor inside a safe box, but on an overall I definitely recommend going there
Amazing must see first printed Bible and history of printing.

It's smallest museum I have ever visited yet one of the coolest. The entrance fee is based on donation. Eventhought there is no english translation, They do have friendly guide downstairs.
According to the description,it is the northern most temple for egyptian god, Isis and Mater magna.

Visit here , If you interested in 
- reading complaint letter to god from 3rd century folks.
- ancient oil lamp
- ritual offering knicks knacks from 3rd  century
- old dates and figs
- dramatic lighting over burial ground.
- connection to greco-roman 
- passing time while waiting for someone else.
Fantastic! Roman history saved, even in a mall. Don't overlook this little gem.
It is nice to see and Free. But not extraordinary
This historical sight is a pre-Roman Temple. There were materials available in many languages as well as guides.
Immer wieder interessante Ausstellungen und historisch hochinteressant. Eintritt frei!

The museum has a good collection of medieval and Baroque art, though it is not presented in a way that makes it easy to follow or appreciate unless you're an expert. The fantastic Roman collection is still mostly in storage, though a small part has finally been returned to the Steinhalle (again the presentation is poor with little information and many objects hard to view).
Bit old fashion. English exist but not enough
Great Experience , nice pieces of art , lightening on paintings was perfect .

Magnificent collection organized by historical period and theme. I don't have a basis of comparison against other European galleries, but the baroque section was unlike anything I've seen at many major US city museums. Well worth the trip.
It was good for people who likes the history. Lots of paintings, statues. They offer route guide map and there are cloak rooms also.

This place took me by surprise,  it is not very big but nice things for especially children to look at, well planned. The small aquarium on the bottom floor is probably one of the coolest things unless you like to check out the dinosaur on the top first 😮...no worries it is not alive...anyhow, fantasy can get ahead of you here so on a rainy day when the kids are bored take a round here and learn something about your history.
Very well presented museum that’s entertaining as well as educational and suitable for all ages. Takes about 3 hours to visit at a leisurely pace.
I don't understand the German, but I enjoy the visit anyway.
It was very clean and nice presentation. We enjoyed visiting the museum.
Great museum with absolutely insane insight at the topics.

The food was wonderful! Good size portions and affordable. The customer service was great. I was really impressed by the complimentary spring roll and cheese cake that came with my meal. Can't wait to go again.
Thai Express offers consistently delicious food and great prices. Today was busy but the food still came quickly. Easily one of my favorite restaurants in town!

It's hard to say which is better, the waitstaff or the food. Both are excellent. This is hands down my favorite Thai place. When eating at the other options in GR I often find myself regretting that I didn't just go to Thai Express instead. Definitely would recommend anyone to at least give it a chance.

Went with 5 others. We were not all served all the same time. My food was last to come out and everyone had already finished their meals. Had to get a to-go container. The inky rain is not a 1 or 2 star is the food was plentiful(when it arrived) and was delicious. Never had Thai before. My new favorite food is Pad Ce ew.
We love the question, "How hot?" and when they say hot... they mean it. Amazing price for the amount we ordered. Great service. Delicious authentic Thai food.
Great collection of stores and services
Nice and beautiful shopping mall
Outside of the Real Markt and Mediamarkt there is not much attraction for me.
Best shopping mall
Besides real,- and MediaMarkt, there is just an average collection of shops located at this small to mid size shopping centre. Closes very early. Lots of free parking.
Not as good not the terrorists have won market is no longer as large dude to safety concerns
Best time ever¡¡¡ If you come to Mainz its a must you enjoy the Market and the German ritual.
Great variety of stalls with fruit, veg, meat, drink, great vibe from all people around the area.

Great place to find some fresh fruits and vegetables! There are also many homemade vines, jams, honeys and other. You can also find there a good place for lunch like backfish, where you can get sandwich or potato salad with fried fish.
Open Air Farmers market with everything from olives & seafood to pickles, honey, herbs, fresh fruit/veg.

Great place. Packed with locals. Good beer and good at reasonable prices. Friendly waiter had me sit at the end of a large table with others already sat - they were friendly too! He was very patient and appreciative of my broken German language skills!
Great hidden gem. Schnitzel and beers are top quality! Warm and cozy in the winter... outdoor seating in the garden in summer. Highly recommend.

Staying nearby and found this nice restaurant on a quiet street next to the Rhine. The service was excellent and the waiters were helpful with recommendations on food and wine! The menu is in German and English and the servers spoke great English - made it easier for me since my German is very weak! I recommend this place for a nice German meal and a GREAT wine list of wines from the region!
Really traditional place with fantastic food, tasty and fresh meal.

I wanted to thank the owners for making me feel very welcome despite the language barrier. My German is almost non-existent but they were kind to work around it, and I had a very lovely first meal in Mainz! Highly recommend the fried potatoes!

My friend recommended this restaurant, and I just visited. 

But, I did not expect the  flavor of cilantro overwhelmingly. Honestly, it was too much for the first time visitor. 

After that, the chef told me, if you notice me that requests the lack of cilantro before the order the regular menu then I could give the less cilantro salsa, and others. 

And he gave me one bag of the chips. 

I am sure that recommend this restaurant for Mexican food, but if you are the first time visitor, you should tell them that they down the level of cilantro or other spices.
Amazing tacos their salsa was amazing. If you get spicy..  they mean it so be careful if you're not used to it!

I work in Kensington and this is one of two places I'll eat at weekly. The burrito is a wicked value. Chicken, beef or pork burrito always are good. Super nice staff. Possibly the best Mexican food in Calgary.
Excellent service, excellent food! The prices were great. Check this place out!

I was muy impressed, awesome service, Great food, awesome portion, Wow, Wow, Wow. This small Restaurant has very big character, I have given only 5 stars here but if I could give more I would. They deserve more that is how good the Food and Customer Service is. Very Well Done Bodega, very well done.
Must visit restaurant in Mainz, delicious food,creative menu and elegant interior ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
Unique neighbourhood restaurant, very authentic and absolutely great food and wines of course. So good that we went twice on a weekend, for lunch and for dinner.
Exellent food, excellent selection of wine, very friendly and witty staff, which sometimes are a bit out of it -- could be a bit more attentive wrt refills. Still, it was a wonderful experience.
Gemütliche, leicht gehobene Weinstube. Schlagfertiger (und netter) Service, Essen sehr gut, grosse Weinauswahl. Echt gut!

Es gehen vier Sterne an die Küche und drei an den Service. Das Essen war geschmacklich und augenscheinlich hervorragend. Allerdings war der Fasan etwas zu trocken. Ansonsten sehr lecker.

Der Service gab uns das Gefühl das wir nicht erwünscht sind. Der Gruß aus der Küche wurde ausgelassen. Das Brot wurde erst nach erneuter Nachfrage zur Vorspeise serviert. 
Die Jacke wurde uns anfangs abgenommen. Als wir gehen wollten, mussten wir die Jacken suchen. 

Trinkgeld in Bar, war dem Blick nach zu Urteilen nicht erwünscht.

Ambiente war auf den ersten Blick schön. Das Bad lässt zu wünschen übrig. Gefühlte 8 Grad. Kein Toilettenpapierhalter. 

Ich hinterlasse faire 3 Sterne.

We love Indian food then we came to visited Indian Tandoori. Appetizer was too oily of course I knew deep fried but seem like they fried while cooking oil not hot yet. Main course looking nice. And last thing found small hair on desert (got appologize). We decided to leave and pay check.
Nice atmosphere and good quality food
Excellent food here! Yummy!
Ordered tikka masala lamb and coudnt chew the meet

Delicious food. Very friendly service and quiet atmosphere. You get delicious starters while waiting for main plate. Mango lassi is little bit too sweet but creamy and full mango flavored, really good. 
One of the best Indian restaurants I've been in. Tasty!

Insanely salty food. The beef tenderloin wasn't very tender. Also, the flavors didn't taste like authentic Thai. (I've been to Thailand many times).  Very disappointing, especially for the high price. The decor is nice and they open late, so those are the plus sides.

Good one can be better especially the service. The food was delicious and the Ambience was nice. The waiters were polite and attentive. We ordered continental, Mexican, Chinese, Thai, Japanese cuisine. Always ask for mineral water..never go for normal water. The service can be better..they take hours to prepare food and serve you .they need to speed up the service especially the continental dishes. This place is good for family get together.. birthday celebrations..etc.
This is the best historic hotel in Kolkata. I love it so much. I went there 2 times i remembered. When i was 12 years old i go there with my family.
The best for thai food. Must try for thai lovers , totally authentic and mouth watering dishes

It is a very  good  Restaurant. All foods fresh and delicious.  
I hope it is really. Never gone there !
Fantastic German cuisine. Great atmosphere with friendly staff. Highly recommend this restaurant.

Fresh food, creatively prepared, delicious and large portion sizes. Great service, friendly, German and English speaking servers. Wonderful atmosphere. This summer, with troublesome wasp populations, I had trouble sitting at my own food. The server promptly brought a smoking quantity of coffee grounds and it completely kept the wasps away! Creative solution! The plum crumble is to die for. The most delicious I've had anywhere!
Wonderful hospitality!
Such a lovely place to spend a summer evening
Great food. Great service. Can't wait for summer to use the patio.
Überschaubare Speisekarte mit vielen leckeren Speisen. Das Schnitzel wie auch das Schweinefilet hat sehr gut geschmeckt. Außerdem wurden wir sehr freundlich bedient.

Diese Restaurant ist absolut Top. Eine kleine Speisekarte, aber alles was angeboten wird schmeckt großartig. Besonders empfehlenswert als Vorspeise das Dreierlei sind drei verschiedene Aufstriche mit Baguette und selbst gebackenem Brot. Für mich 5 Sterne + 1 Stern extra.

Essen war gut
Personal auch locker und gut drauf
Und preiswert ist es auch

Hier bekommt man regionale Küche zu absolut fairen Preisen. Das Jedermann's Schnitzel ist eine Empfehlung wert. Die Portionen sind sehr gut bemessen. Einen Nachtisch kann man auch erst wieder mit zeitlichem Abstand nachlegen, ist aber absolut lecker. Das Servicepersonal ist sehr aufmerksam und zuvorkommend. Der Biergarten ist im Sommer echt schön, denn man kann über die angrenzenden Apfelplantagen der untergehenden Sonne hinterschauen. Gerne wieder.
Sehr lecker nettes Personal gemütlich und ein schöner Aussenbereich
Good food. Excellent service and place.

Delicious food. Excellent service. Reasonable prices. I really enjoyed the cozy atmosphere in this quaint neighborhood restaurant. We enjoyed a full four course meal (for two) for under 70€. If you love Tandoori, then you should stop in for a nice dinner.
Delicious food, especially the lamb korma. Service was reserved but helpful.
Always good, never disappoints
Nice atmosphere, good prices, good and friendly service. The food is decent but not quite as tasty. Possibly inferior ingredients, it's hard to know

Visited with a group of work colleagues, we had a private room upstairs that had a lovely atmosphere but not enough staff to serve a large group of people. I almost wish we were seated downstairs as the place seemed to have a lot more buzz to it. Enjoyed my evening regardless.

Really great food. Had the seasonal pumpkin soup. Wow!  Fantastically good. Everything we had there was great. A hidden gem, by the Mainz Hilton. Almost literally across the street. Not too be missed. A beautiful building, wonderful food and accommodating wait staff.  Please click 'like' if you like my reviews...
This is a great place for going with big groups. Good local cuisine. Love the schnitzel
Great location. Nice service and very good food. Suggested

This is the "go to" restaurant in Mainz, a romantic place in an historic building. The food is outstanding, and a fresh take on traditional German cuisine. It's the place that locals often take out of town guests. It's in a great location in old town
